'But I am not like you . 
The time had been when the Father himself had wept , in the shades of that yard , as his own poor wife had wept . 
He was inclined to remonstrate , and to express his opinion that people who couldn't get on without crying , had no business there . 
On this Sunday evening , he accompanied his brother to the gate with an air of endurance and clemency being in a bland temper and graciously disposed to overlook the tears . 
