But , after the resolution he had made , of course he could have no such merits as these and such a state of mind was nobody's nobody's . 
Mr Gowan made it no concern of his whether it was nobody's or somebody's . 
He preserved his perfect serenity of manner on all occasions , as if the possibility of Clennam's presuming to have debated the great question were too distant and ridiculous to be imagined . 
