Arthur looked at Little Dorrit for help to comprehend this , and was struck by seeing her so timid and red . 
When she answered fervently , she well knew that , she never forgot it , he touched upon his second and more delicate point the suspicion he had formed . 
I have wanted very much to say this to you I have tried for opportunities . 
Don't mind me , who , for the matter of years , might be your father or your uncle . 
Always think of me as quite an old man . 
I know that all your devotion centres in this room , and that nothing to the last will ever tempt you away from the duties you discharge here . 
She was very , very pale , and silently shook her head . 
'It may be , dear Little Dorrit . 
No. No. She shook her head , after each slow repetition of the word , with an air of quiet desolation that he remembered long afterwards . 
The time came when he remembered it well , long afterwards , within those prison walls within that very room . 
'But , if it ever should be , tell me so , my dear child . 
'I press for no confidence now . 
I only ask you to repose unhesitating trust in me . 
