Mr Merdle , left alone to meditate on a better conformation of himself to Society , looked out of nine windows in succession , and appeared to see nine wastes of space . 
Through all the rooms he wandered , as he always did , like the last person on earth who had any business to approach them . 
At last he met the chief butler , the sight of which splendid retainer always finished him . 
CHAPTER A Shoal of Barnacles Mr Henry Gowan and the dog were established frequenters of the cottage , and the day was fixed for the wedding . 
To have got the whole Barnacle family together would have been impossible for two reasons . 
Firstly , because no building could have held all the members and connections of that illustrious house . 
Thus the Barnacles were all over the world , in every direction despatch boxing the compass . 
