Mr Dorrit now interposed , at once to stop these painful subjects by his authority , and to point their moral by his wisdom . 
'My dear , said he to his younger daughter , 'I beg you to ha to say no more . 
Your sister Fanny expresses herself strongly , but not without considerable reason . 
You have now a hum a great position to support . 
That great position is not occupied by yourself alone , but by ha by me , and ha hum by us . 
To be vigilant in making themselves respected . 
Dependants , to respect us , must be ha kept at a distance and hum kept down . 
