Look at this family my family a family more genteel than any lady . 
You have treated this family with disrespect you have been insolent to this family . 
What the reasons of his presumption could be , she was at a loss to imagine but reasons he must have , and they ought to be torn from him . 
But the very genteel lady's English chariot being already horsed and at the inn door , the landlord had slipped up stairs to represent his hard case . 
'Beg your pardon , said the gentleman , detaching himself from the lady , and coming forward . 
'I am a man of few words and a bad hand at an explanation but lady here is extremely anxious that there should be no Row . 
Lady a mother of mine , in point of fact wishes me to say that she hopes no Row . 
Mr Dorrit , still panting under his injury , saluted the gentleman , and saluted the lady , in a distant , final , and invincible manner . 
'No , but really here , old feller you ! This was the gentleman's way of appealing to Edward Dorrit , Esquire , on whom he pounced as a great and providential relief . 
