'I don't think you are well to night , dear Fanny . 
'Stuff and nonsense ! replied the young lady , turning angry again 'I am as well as you are . 
Perhaps I might say better , and yet make no boast of it . 
Poor Little Dorrit , not seeing her way to the offering of any soothing words that would escape repudiation , deemed it best to remain quiet . 
, she didn't want to be forgiven . 
It was not a right example , that she should be constantly stooping to be forgiven by a younger sister . 
And this was the Art of it that she was always being placed in the position of being forgiven , whether she liked it or not . 
As the announcement was vague , though very peremptory , Little Dorrit returned , 'Let us talk about it . 
