Mr Dorrit looked as if he must immediately be driven out of his mind by this account . 
By that time Mr Dorrit had so far recovered from his bewilderment , as to be able to say , in a tolerably connected manner , that he should consider that his duty . 
Flora was delighted with her success , and rose to take her leave . 
He wrote and sent off a brief note excusing himself for that day , and ordered dinner presently in his own rooms at the hotel . 
He had another reason for this . 
He therefore resolved that he would take advantage of that evening's freedom to go down to Clennam and Co . 
